HEADWORD: Silverfish
<hw>Sil"ver*fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The tarpum.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>A white variety of the goldfish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>one of a variety of insects of the order
<ord>Thysanura</ord>, especially <spn>Lepisma saccharina</spn>, which
may infest houses, and eats starched clothing and sized papers. See
<er>Lepisma.</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Silver-gray</ent>⟦br⟧
